 # Description
This algorithm uses a greedy approach to find the city from which a car can complete a circular trip without running out of fuel. 
It goes through each city, calculating the net fuel gain or loss and keeping a running total in the tank. 
Whenever the tank drops below zero, it resets the starting city to the next city, and at the end, it returns the city where starting is guaranteed to work.

